msg.header.defaults: Welcome to the PRISM-ACCESS Open Minds online referral service!

msg.welcome_p1.defaults: Through this website, you can access a referral form to get help directly from a youth mental health worker in your community, for yourself or a young person you care about.

msg.welcome_p1_note.defaults: *Please note that this is a new referral service that is only available to youth 11 to 25 years old in Canada living in Downtown Montreal, Quebec (for youth in homeless situations) and Chatham Kent, Ontario.

msg.welcome_not_emergency.defaults: This is not an emergency service.

msg.welcome_step1_text.defaults: You’ll be asked for some basic information about yourself. There are no right or wrong answers. You can skip questions by clicking “next” or change your information by clicking “back.”

msg.welcome_step2_text.defaults: Once you have completed the form, your referral will be sent to a youth mental health worker in your community. They will contact you within three days, using the method of your choice (e.g., text, phone, email).
